    "synopsis": "Hadeya Etsul, last survivor of a shattered regiment, is folded into a suspicious Cadian tank crew and given command inside the ancient Leman Russ Demolisher Steel Tread. On Croatoas, under the poisonous light of the Great Rift, the Astra Militarum rolls into a death-or-glory offensive against the servants of Chaos while Etsul fights her own memories and a crew that does not trust her. The tank becomes command post, coffin, and confessional at once. A close-quarters war novel where grief, doctrine, and engine heat share the same cramped hull.",
